UI_visible_response: "Cover-Up Class" is a pun that creatively combines the concept of the "proletariat" with the idea of suppressing information. In this context, it humorously refers to individuals or groups who engage in concealing or hiding information, often in a way that parallels the role of the proletariat in Marxist theory. Just as the proletariat represents the working class, the "Cover-Up Class" represents those who work to obscure or suppress truths, often in a systemic or organized manner. This term is likely used in a satirical or critical way to highlight issues of transparency and accountability.
